# Agent 6 — Chat UI

## Contract

Read `agents/06_chat_ui.md` before editing this area. Layout and CLI command surface are defined there.

## Hard rules

- **Two surfaces, same pipeline.** `app/localchat_rag.py` (Streamlit multipage hub: landing, chat, ingestion) and `app/cli.py` (fallback). Chat uses the same `Retriever` + `Answerer`.
- **No business logic in the UI.** Routing, retrieval, generation, and refusal handling live in their owning agents. The UI renders results; it does not decide them.
- **Streaming UX.** Tokens appear as they arrive (`st.write_stream` or equivalent). Sources fill in once the answer completes.
- **Per-answer surface area** (Streamlit):
  - Intent badge: "searched in: people / places / both".
  - "Sources used" expander: entity name + `wikipedia_url` + the chunk text actually shown to the model.
  - Latency in ms.
  - Refusal styling distinct from normal answers.
- **CLI commands** (locked): `:sources` toggle, `:reset` clear chat, `:stats` print store stats, `:quit` exit.
- **Reset semantics.** "Reset chat" clears in-memory turns only. A separate, confirm-guarded "Clear index" calls `VectorStore.reset()` — distinct buttons, distinct intent.
- **State is in-memory.** No on-disk chat history in MVP (stretch only).

## Out of scope here

- Auth, multi-user (single local user — defining constraint of the assignment)
- Conversation memory injected into retrieval (stretch — risks contaminating context)
- Custom theming / heavy CSS — Streamlit defaults are fine
- Modifying `Retriever`, `Answerer`, or store internals — those are Agents 3–5

If the UI needs a piece of data the pipeline doesn't expose, add it to the relevant agent's interface (with their contract update) — don't recompute it in the UI.
